Virtual environments
------------------------
Versions differ for projects
# get rid of conda env (base) with "conda deactivate"

venv -- do not need 3rd party
# use window command prompt

# Create virtualenv: 
> python3 -m venv ENVIRONMENT_NAME 

# Activate virtualenv (Windows): 
(cd into the directory where you created the virtualenv): 

> ENVIRONMENT_NAME\Scripts\activate 

# Activate virtualenv (OS X / Linux): 

> . ENVIRONMENT_NAME/bin/activate 
> source ENVIRONMENT_NAME/bin/activate 
 
# Deactivate virtualenv: 
> deactivate 

# pip is configured with locations that require TLS/SSL, however the ssl module in Python is not available.
--not resolved. Stick with anaconda for now

